HEADWORD: Correption
<hw>Cor*rep"tion</hw> <pr>(k?r-r?p"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>correptio</ets>, <ets>fr</ets>. <ets>corripere</ets> to
seize.]</ety> <def>Chiding; reproof; reproach.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Angry, passionate <qex>correption</qex> being rather apt to
provoke, than to amend.</q> <rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

